  "prompt": "Can non-profit organizations pay a salary?",
  "response": "Yes, non-profit organizations can pay a salary to their employees. Just like any other organization, non-profits need to hire staff to carry out their mission and day-to-day operations. The salaries paid to employees must be reasonable and in line with the organization's budget and financial resources. Non-profit organizations are required to report the salaries of their highest-paid employees on their annual IRS Form 990. However, the key difference between a for-profit and non-profit organization is that the profits generated by a non-profit cannot be distributed to individuals, including employees, as personal income. Any profits must be reinvested back into the organization to further its mission.",
